  "subGoals": [],
  "description": "The RetryBuildStep goal is designed to handle errors encountered during a build step by reading a fix step prompt from a file, executing a language model (LLM) with the relevant information, and validating the results. It retrieves the error message and previous result to generate a prompt for the LLM, which includes the current step\u0027s text, description, previous result, and error message. The goal also validates the module type and method of the result, and if any errors occur during validation, it calls the HandleBuildStepFailure function.",
